# CODEOWNERS
#
# This file tells GitHub who must review changes to which paths. When a pull
# request touches a path listed below, GitHub AUTOMATICALLY requests a review
# from the matching owner. This aligns with the project rule: "Owner gates
# every change."
#
# IMPORTANT: CODEOWNERS only auto-REQUESTS review by itself. To make owner
# review MANDATORY (i.e. block merge until the owner approves), the repo Owner
# must enable branch protection on `main` with "Require review from Code
# Owners" turned on. That is a GitHub repository-settings step and cannot be
# configured from this file alone.
#
# Matching rules: the LAST matching pattern wins. More specific (high-risk)
# entries are placed below the default so they override it for those paths.
# Patterns follow the same syntax as .gitignore.

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Default owner for everything in the repo.
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
* @AmrEbeid

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# High-risk areas — these always require Owner review.
# (Each entry resolves to @AmrEbeid, but is called out explicitly so the
#  intent is clear and so future team additions never weaken these paths.)
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Database migrations — schema and RLS changes are security-critical.
/apps/farm-os/supabase/migrations/ @AmrEbeid

# Database tests (pgTAP) — guard the security/invariant oracles.
/apps/farm-os/supabase/tests/ @AmrEbeid

# Server actions — privileged server-side mutations / authz boundaries.
/apps/farm-os/app/**/actions.ts @AmrEbeid

# Supabase client wiring — service-role / auth-sensitive client setup.
/apps/farm-os/lib/supabase/ @AmrEbeid

# Auth helpers — authentication and access-control logic.
/apps/farm-os/lib/auth.ts @AmrEbeid

# Published UI library — changes here ship to all consumers.
/packages/ui/ @AmrEbeid
